---
import StorybookEmbed from '../../components/StorybookEmbed.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Segmented Control — AA Design System</title>
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 900px;
             margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem; color: #00081C; }
      .back { display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 2rem;
              color: #666; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.875rem; }
      table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
      th, td { padding: 8px 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left; }
      th { background: #f5f5f5; }
      .guidance { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
                  gap: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
      .guidance-col h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
      .guidance-col ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
      .guidance-col li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
      .do h3 { color: #00703C; }
      .dont h3 { color: #D4351C; }
      .general h3 { color: #00081C; }
      .storybook-placeholder { border: 2px dashed #ccc; padding: 2rem;
             text-align: center; color: #666; border-radius: 4px; margin: 1rem 0; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`} class="back">&larr; Home</a>
    <h1>Segmented Control</h1>
    <p>A segmented control lets you switch between a small set of related options, with one clear choice active at a time.</p>

    <h2>Live component</h2>
    <StorybookEmbed story="components-segmented-control--two-options" viewMode="story" />

    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <div class="guidance">
      <div class="guidance-col do">
        <h3>✓ Use segmented control</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Switching between 2–4 closely related options</li>
          <li>Changing views, filters, or modes on the same content</li>
          <li>When the result updates instantly</li>
          <li>When options are equal in importance</li>